{
  "text": "Although 4-digit PIN codes, which are currently the most common way of granting access to information stored on the device, provide similar benefits in terms of usability, it seems unlikely that their security could be enhanced with keystroke dynamics analyses on touch-screen devices, given that the size of a PIN code is too small and that previous studies have shown that large training sets are required to achieve good performances on touch-screens [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, other studies have shown that it is more difficult for users to remember different PINs over extended periods of time than graphical passwords [CITATION_2] .",
